//- route 2: renders a page that displays a form which is your search bar.
//- takes in the post request from your form, then displays matching users on a new page. Users should be matched based on whether either their first or last name contains the input string.
//- Your site has a form on it that acts like a search bar.
//- On click, it should retrieve a list of matching users and list them by name on the same page.

html
	include includes/head.pug
	body
		.main.container
			.row
				.col-md-6.col-md-offset-3
					h1.display-4.m-b-2 Search
					form(id="searchForm")
						div.form-group
							input.form-control(list='suggestions',id='searchInput',name='name', placeholder='Search for a name')
							datalist(id='suggestions')
								//- option(value="Yo")
						div.form-group
							button.btn.btn-primary(id='searchSubmit',type='submit') Search
